		<section class="type t2">
		    <div class="header">
			<h1>Modelling the transport</h1>
		    </div>


		    <div class="tf mt-2">
			<div class="col">
			    <img class="mt-2" src="assets/images/cell/diffusion.png" height="580px">
			</div>
			
			<div class="col">
			    <p>Two-state Markovian run-and-tumble particle model of cell<br>
				Exponential distributions for stop and go times <br>
				MSD is found to be
				\[
				\begin{align}
				\Delta(\tau) &= 2\hat{v}_0^2 \Bigl(\tau\,\langle\tau_\mathrm{g}\rangle - \langle\tau_\mathrm{g}\rangle^{\,2}\left(1 - e^{\tau/\langle\tau_\mathrm{g}\rangle}\right)\Bigr),\\
				\hat{v}_0 &= \sqrt{\bar{v}^2 + \sigma_v^2},
				\end{align}
				\]
				where $\bar{v}$ and $\sigma_v^2$ are the mean and the variance of the full velocity distribution<br>
				For short time scales
				$$\Delta \left(\tau\right) \simeq (\hat{v}_0\, \tau)^2,$$
				and long time scales
				$$\Delta \left(\tau \right) \simeq \hat{D}\,\tau, \quad \hat{D}=2\, \hat{v}_0^{2}\, \langle\tau_\mathrm{g}\rangle$$
				
			    </p>
			</div>
			
		    </div>


		    <div class="footer">
		    </div>
		</section>

