				We look at the isoperimetric ratio (IPR)
				\[
				IPR=\langle \frac{P}{\sqrt{A}} \rangle
				\]
				Describing cell shape - for circle $IPR=3.55$<br>
				Packing fraction defined as
				\[
				\phi=\frac{1}{A_{arena}}\sum_i^N A_i
				\]
				Sharp increase in IPR at $\phi=0.9$ - disk jamming<br>
				Transition in IPR at around $3.8$ 
			    </p>
